"title": "5736: singleness",
"media_type": "Text",
"index_reference": "5736: singleness",
"language": "eng",
"review_level": "None",
"content": "<p>Not being married; the state prior to betrothal or following separation or the death of a spouse. In Scripture, an unmarried woman generally lives with, and is the responsibility of, her family. Whilst the unmarried are freer of worldly concerns and may devote themselves more fully to God, those already married should not separate, and those without the gift of celibacy should not remain single.</p>\n<h2>Responsibility for an unmarried woman</h2>\n<h3>An unmarried woman is responsible to her father</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:16\">DEU 22:16</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod2:21\">EXO 2:21</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Num30:3-Num30:5\">NUM 30:3–30:5</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg1:12-Judg1:13\">JDG 1:12–1:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:17\">1SA 18:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam18:21\">1SA 18:21</a></p>\n<h3>An unmarried woman is dependent on her brothers</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev21:3\">LEV 21:3</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen24:51\">GEN 24:51</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen34:14-Gen34:15\">GEN 34:14–34:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ezek44:25\">EZK 44:25</a></p>\n<h3>Widowed or divorced women could return to their parents' home</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Ruth1:8-Ruth1:13\">RUT 1:8–1:13</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen38:11\">GEN 38:11</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Lev22:13\">LEV 22:13</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg19:2\">JDG 19:2</a></p>\n<h2>Regulations relating to the unmarried</h2>\n<p><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut20:7\">DEU 20:7</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:20-Deut22:21\">DEU 22:20–22:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Deut22:28-Deut22:29\">DEU 22:28–22:29</a></p>\n<h2>The unwelcome prospect of remaining unmarried</h2>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Judg11:37-Judg11:39\">JDG 11:37–11:39</a></strong>; <strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:6\">ISA 54:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gen19:31-Gen19:32\">GEN 19:31–19:32</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa49:20-Isa49:21\">ISA 49:20–49:21</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa62:4\">ISA 62:4</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Hos2:2\">HOS 2:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Gal4:27\">GAL 4:27</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Isa54:1\">ISA 54:1</a></p>\n<h2>Celibacy</h2>\n<h3>Celibacy is a calling from God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:7\">1CO 7:7</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Jer16:2\">JER 16:2</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt19:10-Matt19:121\">MAT 19:10–19:121</a>CO <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt7:9\">7:9</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:36\">1CO 7:36</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:11-1Tim5:14\">1TI 5:11–5:14</a></p>\n<h3>Believers should remain as they are when called</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:25-1Cor7:28\">1CO 7:25–7:28</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:10\">1CO 7:10</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:12-1Cor7:13\">1CO 7:12–7:13</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:17\">1CO 7:17</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:24\">1CO 7:24</a></p>\n<h3>Sexual abstinence within marriage is strictly limited</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:2-1Cor7:6\">1CO 7:2–7:6</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Exod19:15\">EXO 19:15</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Sam21:4-1Sam21:5\">1SA 21:4–21:5</a></p>\n<h3>The desirability of being unmarried</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:8\">1CO 7:8</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:1\">1CO 7:1</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:11\">1CO 7:11</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:37-1Cor7:38\">1CO 7:37–7:38</a></p>\n<h3>The unmarried may devote themselves to God</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:32-1Cor7:35\">1CO 7:32–7:35</a></strong> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:20\">LUK 14:20</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke14:26\">LUK 14:26</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Acts21:9\">ACT 21:9</a>; <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Tim5:5\">1TI 5:5</a></p>\n<h3>Marriage belongs to a passing order</h3>\n<p><strong><a href=\"https://ref.ly/Matt22:30\">MAT 22:30</a></strong> parallels <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Mark12:25\">MRK 12:25</a>, <a href=\"https://ref.ly/Luke20:35\">LUK 20:35</a> <em>See also</em> <a href=\"https://ref.ly/1Cor7:29-1Cor7:31\">1CO 7:29–7:31</a></p>",
